On Mon, 27 Feb 1995, Andrew Lowery wrote:

> How does one mark all of the postings in a particular newsgroup as read 
> in pine.  In rn, for instance, the keystroke is "c", to catch-up on all 
> articles.  Any help will be appreciated.
> 
 
1.  Go to main Pine menu, choose Setup; select "configure":  In selection
menu, place "x" in "Enable aggregate command set".
 
2.  In any newsgroup, to catch up or to delete a range of articles,
various aggregate commands are available.  To delete all the articles,
type ;aad  which translates "select all, apply delete".
 
Thanks to Garland Boyd for this one...

	-Andrew Lowery
	 


