On Wed, 1 Mar 1995, Juanita Fischer wrote:

> Is there a way to check for new mail from the command line without 
> entering pine?

That is what I do... use pico to edit a text file containing the following:

finger.sun keviny|grep "New mail"
finger.sun keviny|grep unread
finger.sun keviny|grep Unread
finger.sun keviny|grep "Mail last read"

Substitute finger.sun and keviny with your local finger command and your 
user-id respectively.  Then, type "chmod u+x <filename>" to make it 
executable.  I hope this helps.

