> 
WADR, I think the point is that, where there is a need for BCC, there is 
a need for the BCC recipients to know that the TOs and CCs don't know 
that the BCCs have a copy.  

A couple of reasons we use BCC are:
-  Don't was TOs and CCs to know about the BCCs for CYA reasons
-  Don't want to provide a list of email contacts besides sender and 
   limited CCs.

If it is really important that the BCCs know they are being blind copied, 
we forward a copy of the message TO them, prepending a note explaining 
that the following message was sent... and they are being provided with a 
blind copy.

VTR
Don 
