I don't have any problems with what you suggest above. But, I think Pine
already does that. I wonder if you ever used Pine yourself. But, when
you hit R, Pine asks you if you want post a followup to the Usenet. The
default is NO. If you hit the return button your answer goes only via
e-mail. Even if you press Y. After you are done and ready to send it again
says this time "this might go to thousands of people do you want to do
that?" If you find these messages cryptic and have better suggestions go
ahead it's fine with me. Also, it is not very difficult to know if a message
has arrived from news or email with Pine. I don't know all the possible
setups. But, here, my incoming folders, private folders and news folders
are clearly separated. The only time I might be confused is when I save
a news message to a private folder and forget where it came from. Ok, that
part can be enhanced and again no problem.

Now, for the etiquette: there are some very hot groups. Sometimes, somebody
gets very angry with what you have said there and sends you an email with
threats and/or curses. In such a case, I don't think that it is a breach
of netiquette to reply on the Usenet. 

