You don't.

Pine is a program for reading electronic mail that has been sent to you.  
It can also be used for reading Usenet News articles and also posting 
your own to the Usenet News system.

Pine is not a World-Wide Web browser (a thing which lets you view pages 
from the Web), nor is it an editor (which you normally use to create such 
pages yourself).

You should probably be using an editor to create your Web pages, and 
check them using a Web Browser such as Mosaic or Netscape (for X 
workstations, micros, etc) or Lynx (terminal screen based without the 
fancy graphics).

If you need more help try asking in the comp.infosystems.users Usenet 
News group.

