Michael, 
This behavior has nothing to do with posting, it's just the way Pine
displays the index of the messages you are *reading*... 

As Selcuk said, Pine figures you already know what your own name is, so when
a message in the Index is from you, it displays the *recipient* name in 
the index instead of your name. 

(If you get a different result using another program to post it's only
because that other program uses a different form of your name, so Pine
doesn't recognize the message as from you.)

-teg

