I think it would be good advice not to set up a strawman so crudely.
Why do you insist that following up from a folder rather than from the
newsgroup somehow magically takes it out of context?  If you wait two
weeks, sure, but not if you wait a few hours or even a day or two.
Given some of the stuff I read, I'd think it would be a good idea for
most users *not* to post until they think about it some.  

