Well, upon further investigation it appears that the problem is related
to the fact that the system that we're running on has short filesystem
names (limited to 14 characters).  (HP-UX supports long names, but we're
using 14 for "historical" reasons.)  What's happening is that the
locking routine bezerk_lock() tries to create a pair of lock files
linked together, but the second creation fails because the name is not
unique at the point where the additional info is tacked onto the
original file name.

Has anyone else run into this problem, and if so, is there a simple
solution (other than converting to long filenames)?
