The only place that could know for sure that something was posted AND
mailed is the source. The source cannot know positively that something
was not posted. Assuming that it was not would be an error on the safe
side.

But this leaves us back at the destination being the one creating the
flag. (The source can only tell us what it thinks will happen; the
destination can tell us how the article actually arrived.) And, since
trn already creates this flag, maybe others should follow suit.



